####TUmor growth curves
##################Repeat for the volume STS13
Volume_growth <- as.data.frame(read_excel("tumor_measurement_GABA.xlsx", 
    sheet = "Tumor_volume_STS13")) #Data available upon request

##Re-format
melt_tmp<-melt(Volume_growth,id.vars = "day",measure.vars = colnames(Volume_growth)[-1])
melt_tmp$Treatment<-gsub(pattern = "[_].*","",melt_tmp$variable)
##Calculate area under the curve for each mouse
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(MESS)  # For AUC calculation
# Calculate AUC for each mouse
melt_tmp<-melt_tmp[!is.na(melt_tmp$value),]
###To properly evaluate curves we have to cut in this particular experiment to day 22, otherwise the values for PD1 and combo will be higher when compared to controls...

auc_data <- melt_tmp[melt_tmp$day<=22,] %>%
  group_by(variable, Treatment) %>%
  summarise(AUC = auc(day, value))

# View the AUC data
print(auc_data)

###Evaluate normality of distribution  ShapiroâWilk test
# Perform Shapiro-Wilk test for each treatment group
shapiro_results <- auc_data %>%
  group_by(Treatment) %>%
  summarise(p_value = shapiro.test(AUC)$p.value)

print(shapiro_results)

# Check if all groups pass the normality test
normality_pass <- all(shapiro_results$p_value > 0.05)
print(normality_pass)
# Perform the appropriate test
#shapiro_A$p.value > 0.05 & shapiro_B$p.value > 0.05 ... then t.test
#else....wilcox.test
# if (shapiro_A$p.value > 0.05 & shapiro_B$p.value > 0.05) {
#   auc_test <- t.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data)
# } else {
#   auc_test <- wilcox.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data)
# }



#For comparisons with PBS (or controls), two-tailed P values are shown. For comparisons of combination therapies versus PD1 blockade alone, one-tailed P valuesare shown based on null hypothesis that combinations will improveoutcomes compared to PD1 blockade alone.


auc_data$Treatment<-factor(auc_data$Treatment,levels = c("PD1+3MPA","PD1","3MPA","Control"))


###Two side test for comparing vs controls..
auc_test_PD1_PBS <- t.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data[auc_data$Treatment%in%c("Control","PD1"),],alternative="two.sided") #Test 
#
auc_test_PD1_3MPA <- t.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data[auc_data$Treatment%in%c("PD1","3MPA"),],alternative="two.sided") #Test 

###Two side test for comparing vs controls..
auc_test_combo_PBS <- t.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data[auc_data$Treatment%in%c("Control","PD1+3MPA"),],alternative="two.sided") #Test 
#
auc_test_combo_3MPA <- t.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data[auc_data$Treatment%in%c("3MPA","PD1+3MPA"),],alternative="two.sided") #Test 

###Between controls
auc_test_PBS_3MPA <- t.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data[auc_data$Treatment%in%c("3MPA","Control"),],alternative="two.sided") 

####Combo vs PD1 can be evaluated at day 28..
###
auc_data <- melt_tmp[melt_tmp$day<=28,] %>%
  group_by(variable, Treatment) %>%
  summarise(AUC = auc(day, value))

# View the AUC data
print(auc_data)
auc_data$Treatment<-factor(auc_data$Treatment,levels = c("PD1+3MPA","PD1","3MPA","Control"))

auc_test_PD1_combo <- t.test(AUC ~ Treatment, data = auc_data[auc_data$Treatment%in%c("PD1+3MPA","PD1"),],alternative="less") #Test combo has lower growth than PD1...


##Evaluate means accordingly..
# Calculate mean and SEM for each day and treatment group
data<-melt_tmp
summary_data <- data %>%
  group_by(day, Treatment) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_TumorArea = mean(value),
    sem_TumorArea = sd(value) / sqrt(n())
  )

# View the summary data
print(summary_data)


# Extract the p-values
auc_test_PD1_PBS <- paste("p-value =", format(auc_test_PD1_PBS$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = F))
auc_test_PD1_combo <- paste("p-value =", format(auc_test_PD1_combo$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = F))
auc_test_PD1_3MPA <- paste("p-value =", format(auc_test_PD1_3MPA$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = F))
auc_test_combo_PBS <- paste("p-value =", format(auc_test_combo_PBS$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = F))
auc_test_combo_3MPA <- paste("p-value =", format(auc_test_combo_3MPA$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = F))
auc_test_PBS_3MPA <- paste("p-value =", format(auc_test_PBS_3MPA$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = F))

custom_colors<-c("PD1+3MPA"="#e71d36ff","3MPA"="#2ec4b6ff","PD1"="#ff9f1cff","Control"="#bdd5eaff")
# Create the plot
p <- ggplot(summary_data, aes(x = day, y = mean_TumorArea, color = Treatment, group = Treatment)) +
  geom_line(size = 1.5) +  # Line for the mean tumor area
  geom_point(size = 3) +  # Points for the mean tumor area
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_TumorArea - sem_TumorArea, ymax = mean_TumorArea + sem_TumorArea), width = 0.2) +  # Error bars
  labs(
    title = "Tumor volume Over Time by Treatment",
    x = "Days",
    y = "Tumor Volume (mm^3)"
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(values = custom_colors)+
  theme_std() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
    legend.title = element_blank()
  ) +geom_vline(xintercept = c(10, 16, 21), linetype = "dashed", color = "black")##Lines when treatment with aPD1 was performed

p<-p+ annotate("text", x = max(summary_data$day)+1, y = c(1600,1400,1200,1000,800,600)[1], label = paste0(auc_test_PBS_3MPA, " (PBS vs 3MPA)"), hjust = 1)+
  annotate("text", x = max(summary_data$day)+1, y = c(1600,1400,1200,1000,800,600)[2], label = paste0(auc_test_PD1_PBS, " (aPD1 vs PBS)"), hjust = 1)+
  annotate("text", x = max(summary_data$day)+1, y = c(1600,1400,1200,1000,800,600)[3], label = paste0(auc_test_PD1_3MPA, " (aPD1 vs 3MPA)"), hjust = 1)+
  annotate("text", x = max(summary_data$day)+1, y = c(1600,1400,1200,1000,800,600)[4], label = paste0(auc_test_combo_PBS, " (Combo vs PBS)"), hjust = 1)+
  annotate("text", x = max(summary_data$day)+1, y = c(1600,1400,1200,1000,800,600)[5], label = paste0(auc_test_combo_3MPA, " (Combo vs 3MPA)"), hjust = 1)+
  annotate("text", x = max(summary_data$day)+1, y = c(1600,1400,1200,1000,800,600)[6], label = paste0(auc_test_PD1_combo, " (Combo vs aPD1)"), hjust = 1)

# Display the plot
print(p)

##Save plot..

ggsave(filename = "Tumor_Volume_STS13.pdf",p,width = 10,height = 8)

Mice_data<-as.data.frame(read_excel(path = "survival_STS.xlsx")) #Data only available upon request to authors
#Use movics
library(MOVICS)


for (z in unique(Mice_data$Experiment)) {
  ##Subset data
  Mice_data_tmp<-Mice_data[Mice_data$Experiment==z,]
  ##Do a movics like object...
  
pseudo.moic.res  <- list("clust.res" = Mice_data_tmp[,c("mouse","Group")],
                                        "mo.method" = "PAM50")
rownames(pseudo.moic.res$clust.res)<-pseudo.moic.res$clust.res$mouse
# make pseudo samID
pseudo.moic.res$clust.res$samID <- rownames(pseudo.moic.res$clust.res)
#pseudo.moic.res$clust.res$clust <- ifelse(pseudo.moic.res$clust.res$RECIST_R_nR==tmp2,1,2) #Re-label, NR=CS1
##Perform a KM for 500 mm3 per experiment
pseudo.moic.res$clust.res$clust <-pseudo.moic.res$clust.res$Group
##Convert survival time
Mice_data_tmp$fustat<-as.numeric(Mice_data_tmp$Censor_500)
Mice_data_tmp$futime<-as.numeric(Mice_data_tmp$Day_500)#Must be in days
rownames(Mice_data_tmp)<-Mice_data_tmp$mouse


  
surv.validation_pam <- compSurv(moic.res         = pseudo.moic.res,
                     surv.info        = Mice_data_tmp,
                     convt.time       = "d", # leave in days
                     surv.median.line = "hv", # switch to both
                     fig.name         = paste0("KM_500_Experiment_",z)
                     ,p.adjust.method ="none") 
  
  #Repeat for 1000m3 (STS15 not available...)

##Convert survival time
Mice_data_tmp$fustat<-as.numeric(Mice_data_tmp$Censor_1000)
Mice_data_tmp$futime<-as.numeric(Mice_data_tmp$Day_1000)#Must be in days
rownames(Mice_data_tmp)<-Mice_data_tmp$mouse


  
surv.validation_pam <- compSurv(moic.res         = pseudo.moic.res,
                     surv.info        = Mice_data_tmp,
                     convt.time       = "d", # leave in days
                     surv.median.line = "hv", # switch to both
                     fig.name         = paste0("KM_100_Experiment_",z)
                     ,p.adjust.method ="none") 


  
}
